trackmate-py — Authors and Acknowledgements
============================================

trackmate-py is a pure-Python port of TrackMate's spot detection
subsystem. It is a derivative work of the upstream TrackMate Java
project and is distributed under the same GNU General Public License,
version 3 (or later).


Original work
-------------

TrackMate Java codebase (the canonical reference implementation that
this project translates):

    Copyright (C) 2010 - 2026 TrackMate developers.

    Lead author: Jean-Yves Tinevez (Institut Pasteur, Paris)
    Project home: https://imagej.net/plugins/trackmate
    Source: https://github.com/trackmate-sc/TrackMate

The detector classes specifically translated by this project are:

    fiji.plugin.trackmate.detection.DogDetector
    fiji.plugin.trackmate.detection.LogDetector
    fiji.plugin.trackmate.detection.HessianDetector
    fiji.plugin.trackmate.detection.DetectionUtils

…together with the supporting imglib2 helpers
(LocalExtrema / SubpixelLocalization, HessianMatrix, PartialDerivative,
FFTConvolution / FFTMethods) and the Mines JTK prime-factor FFT engine
(edu.mines.jtk.dsp.{Pfacc, FftReal, FftComplex}) that TrackMate's
LogDetector invokes through imglib2-algorithm-fft.

Mines JTK is originally distributed under the Apache License 2.0
(Copyright (C) 2003 - 2017 Colorado School of Mines), and has been
relicensed to GPL v3 here as permitted by Apache 2.0 § 4(b) when
incorporated into a GPL-licensed combined work.

imglib2-algorithm-fft is originally distributed under a BSD 2-clause
license, which is GPL-compatible.


Translation and port author
---------------------------

    Digin Dominic
    https://github.com/digin1

    Translation date: 2026-04-07
    Original publication: <to be added when first tagged release lands>

Digin is the sole author of:

  * the Python translations under trackmate_py/
  * the wrapper scripts run_trackmate_python_headless.py,
    run_trackmate_fiji_headless.py
  * the numba metric accelerators in _metric_helpers_numba.py
  * the per-spot FWHM ellipse fit, KDTree dedup, confidence
    columns, and visualization helpers


Citation
--------

If you use trackmate-py in published work, please cite the original
TrackMate paper:

    Tinevez, J.-Y., Perry, N., Schindelin, J., Hoopes, G. M., Reynolds,
    G. D., Laplantine, E., Bednarek, S. Y., Shorte, S. L., & Eliceiri,
    K. W. (2017). TrackMate: An open and extensible platform for
    single-particle tracking. Methods, 115, 80-90.
    https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2016.09.016
